<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 03 at 3:36AM EDT  by NWS Boston</headline>
<description>...ELEVATED FIRE WEATHER CONCERNS THIS AFTERNOON...
An anomalously dry airmass for early April remains over the region
Monday morning. As temperatures rise into the low and mid 50s this
Monday afternoon, minimum relative humidities will drop to 30 to
35 percent. This combined with increasing southwest winds 15 to 25
mph will result in elevated fire weather concerns this afternoon.</description>
